I personally strongly recommend you take at least 53 and EE16B for 189, webcast.berkeley.edu and MIT OCW would be good resources

children.subject: hoping for one more try for workload opinions on some of the above classes listed.
I would put 61C in medium in the above answer and 164 and 189 would be significantly heavier than 170.
I would put EE 16a lighter than anything here, in a category called very light.

I’ll disagree with the anon directly above me here about EE16A - if you’re looking to compare workloads between classes, and as a freshman you’ve only really taken 16A, it is sort of unfair to say thT 16A was very light and that everything else would be much more time. 

Personally, I spent a TON of time on the 16A problem sets because I didn’t really know linear algebra before 16A, and circuits are hard. I’ve taken 164 and 189 and 61C and I spent more time per week on 16A than I did in 61C and 164. 

It really depends on how intense you get with 16A. For some people, it was no time at all, but for me it took a lot of time...

I think all of the relative rankings given above are accurate, but just keep in mind that if you’re using 16A as your baseline, there is a lot of variance there in people’s experience. Upper divs aren’t as crazy as they look at first!

I agree with Alex's sentiments about EE 16A. I had a similar experience, and also spent more time on it per week than 162 (not 164, haven't taken it) or 61C, and I dare say even EE 126. You'll get people all across the spectrum with what they thought of it, largely depending on when they took it in their time here.
164 probably depends a lot on prof. I took it this past semester with Sen and honestly it felt much lighter than 170 and arguably even 16A.

thanks!  Ideally, I'd like to collate the classes listed above into 3 piles, heavy, medium, and light, and then take one from each pile every semester.  My understanding is that 164 and 169 is also on the heavy side along with 189 and STAT 140/ EECS 126, are there others in the heavy pile?

I unfortunately (to some degree) am in a situation where all I have left are pretty much technicals after the end of my first year.  So I will have to take forced combinations of CS/EE/INFO classes that may or may not be suitable.  Please rate in terms of workload, using CS61A and CS70 as the bar (I consider 61A light to medium, CS70 medium to heavy at times).  I'm a very good programmer, above average in abstract concepts, average in math. All my CS LD classes are done except for 61C.  Want to finish the list below off, plus 2-3 other electives, in 3, maybe 4 semesters.

CS61C
Data 100
STAT 140 or EECS 126
CS 186
CS 188
CS 189 or INDENG 142 (I haven't taken Math 53 yet, don't really want to but I will if I have to)
CS 170
CS 169
CS 164
COGSCI 131
